thread.title_full: Notre Dame's Coco Chen, Logan Lencheski win District 11 AA doubles title in classic

title: Notre Dame's Coco Chen, Logan Lencheski win District 11 AA doubles title in classic
text:
Notre Dame's Logan Lencheski, left, and Coco Chen captured district doubles gold on Monday. (Josh Folck | For lehighvalleylive.com) By Josh Folck | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 19, 2015 5:53 PM, updated October 19, 2015 6:07 PM View/Post Comments 
Coco Chen/Logan Lencheski (Notre Dame) def. Brenna Magliochetti/Molly Ehrig (Bethlehem Catholic) 6-3, 2-6, 7-5 â€” Rapid Recap 
Notre Dame senior Coco Chen and freshman Logan Lencheski won a three-set classic over Bethlehem Catholic 's Brenna Magliochetti and Molly Ehrig 6-3, 2-6, 7-5 to clinch the District 11 Class AA doubles title on Monday at Lehigh University. 
Turning point : With the third set tied at 5-5, the Crusaders duo battled to victories in the next two games to clinch the championship. Left-hander Lencheski delivered an ace to put the Crusaders up 6-5 and then Chen put the match away with a strong forehand down the middle of the court to secure the championship on Notre Dame's third match point of the game. 
What it means : It's the first District 11 girls tennis title in Notre Dame school history. It's also the first one for Chen after advancing to the finals in the singles and doubles tournaments in each of the last two seasons. The Crusaders' senior and freshman pair will head to the state tournament on Nov. 6 in Hershey. For Magliochetti and Ehrig, it was a very impressive showing for a freshman and a sophomore.
